</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eONOlN iAhVxb pf-51_ pf-text-1"><strong>Children (1 to puberty)</strong> - Use one hand for chest compressions if sufficient, or two hands if required, compressing at least one-third of the depth of the chest at the same rate as for adults.





























